---
name: terraform-testing
description: Deep Terraform provider testing for individual Gcore resources with intelligent test case generation. Use when thoroughly testing a SINGLE Terraform resource by examining old/new provider code, identifying special API calls, computed fields, and edge cases. Claude analyzes source code to determine what needs testing rather than using templates. Includes real infrastructure validation, mitmproxy API tracking, and automated cleanup.
---

# Terraform Testing Skill

This skill provides deep, intelligent testing for individual Gcore Terraform provider resources, focusing on thorough analysis of ONE resource at a time.

## Phase-Based Testing Workflow (Quickstart)

| Phase | Description | Key Actions | References |
|-------|-------------|-------------|------------|
| **1. ANALYZE** | Examine resource structure | Scan OpenAPI, SDK, model.go; Compare with legacy provider; Check JIRA for edge cases | [OpenAPI Access](#check-against-openapi-spec), [Old Provider Comparison](#old-provider-comparison-testing), [JIRA Integration](references/jira_integration.md) |
| **2. PLAN** | Create coverage matrix & get approval | Map ALL union variants, computed fields, special endpoints to tests; User must approve | [Testing Plan Template](#testing-plan-template), [Resource Coverage Matrix](#resource-coverage-matrix) |
| **3. SETUP** | Prepare environment | Verify .terraformrc, rebuild provider, load credentials, start mitmproxy | [Pre-Test Setup](#-critical-pre-test-setup) |
| **4. EXECUTE** | Run tests with MITM capture | Test each variant, capture API calls, verify payloads | [Union Type Testing](#union-type-testing-critical), [MITM Verification](#api-call-verification-with-mitmproxy) |
| **5. VALIDATE** | Check drift & behavior | Run plan after each apply, verify no drift, check all QA categories | [Drift Testing](#drift-testing-most-critical), [QA Checklist](references/qa_checklist.md) |
| **6. REPORT** | Document & store evidence | Complete report template, store artifacts, cleanup resources | [Evidence Package](#evidence-package-requirements), [Report Template](references/test_report_template.md) |

**⚠️ STOP at each phase boundary. Do not proceed to next phase without completing all requirements.**

---

## Core Principles

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Never make conclusions based on source code analysis alone. All hypotheses MUST be validated through real infrastructure testing.**

## ⚠️ MANDATORY: Present Testing Plan for Approval

**Before running ANY tests on real infrastructure, you MUST:**

1. **Analyze the resource** - Examine OpenAPI spec, SDK code, and model.go for union types
2. **Create a comprehensive testing plan** that includes:
   - All union type variants to be tested
   - All fields with computed_optional that need drift testing
   - Special API endpoints to verify via MITM
   - Dependencies required (networks, volumes, etc.)
3. **Present the plan to the user** in a clear format
4. **Wait for user approval** before proceeding

### Testing Plan Template

```markdown
## Testing Plan: [Resource Name]

### Phase 1: Analysis Summary

#### OpenAPI → SDK Alignment
| API Operation | SDK Method | Async? | Notes |
|---------------|------------|--------|-------|
| POST /resource | NewAndPoll | Yes | |
| PATCH /resource | UpdateAndPoll | Yes | |
| DELETE /resource | DeleteAndPoll | Yes | |
| Special: /attach | AttachAndPoll | Yes | Not in SDK? |

#### Legacy Provider Comparison
| Feature | Old Provider | New Provider | Parity? |
|---------|-------------|--------------|---------|
| Create | WaitTaskAndReturn | NewAndPoll | ✅ |
| Update | HasChange logic | MarshalForPatch | ⚠️ Check |
| Unset | Unset endpoint | ? | ❌ Missing |

#### Migration Nuances
- [ ] Special endpoints (unset, attach, detach)
- [ ] Field clearing behavior (empty array vs null)
- [ ] Computed field defaults

#### JIRA/Known Issues
- GCLOUD-XXXX: [description] → Test case #N
- GCLOUD-YYYY: [description] → Test case #M

---

### Phase 2: Resource Coverage Matrix

**Every row must map to at least one test. Reviewer must sign off before tests run.**

#### Union Type Coverage
| Field | Variant | Discriminator | Required Fields | Test # | QA Categories |
|-------|---------|---------------|-----------------|--------|---------------|
| volumes | image | source: "image" | image_id, size | 1 | drift, create |
| volumes | existing-volume | source: "existing-volume" | volume_id | 2 | drift, create |
| volumes | new-volume | source: "new-volume" | size, type_name | 3 | drift, create |
| interfaces | external | type: "external" | - | 4 | drift, create |
| interfaces | subnet | type: "subnet" | network_id, subnet_id | 5 | drift, create |

#### Computed/Optional Field Coverage
| Field | Tag | Default Value | Test # | Drift Check? |
|-------|-----|---------------|--------|--------------|
| size | computed_optional | - | 1,2,3 | Yes |
| delete_on_termination | computed_optional | false | 1 | Yes |
| status | computed | - | All | Yes |

#### Special API Endpoint Coverage
| Endpoint | Purpose | Test # | MITM Pattern |
|----------|---------|--------|--------------|
| POST /resource | Create | 1-5 | Check payload |
| PATCH /resource | Update | 6 | Check PATCH body |
| /attach_interface | Attach | 7 | Verify special endpoint |

#### QA Checklist Mapping
| QA Category | Test # | Expected Behavior |
|-------------|--------|-------------------|
| Drift detection | 1-5 | No changes on 2nd plan |
| Update in-place | 6 | Same ID after update |
| Async operations | 1-5 | Task polling works |
| Empty array handling | 8 | Sends [] not null |
| Import | 9 | State matches API |
| Error handling | 10 | Clear error message |

